Package: SSNdesign
Title: An R Package for Optimal and Adaptive Sampling Designs on Stream Networks
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
  person("Alan", "Pearse", email = "apearse9@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
  person("James", "McGree", email = "james.mcgree@qut.edu.au", role = c("aut")),
  person("Nicholas", "Som", email = "nicholas_som@fws.gov", role = c("aut")),
  person("Jay", "Ver Hoef", email = "jay.verhoef@noaa.gov", role = c("aut")),
  person("Erin", "Peterson", email = "erin.peterson@qut.edu.au", role = c("aut"))
  )
Author: Alan Pearse [aut, cre], James McGree [aut], Nicholas Som [aut], Jay Ver Hoef [aut], Erin Peterson [aut] 
Maintainer: Alan Pearse <apearse9@gmail.com>
Description: Solve pseudo-Bayesian optimal and adaptive sampling design problems 
	on stream networks. Given a geostatistical stream network model and a utility function, this 
	package will optimise a sampling design so that one gets the best information from their stream
	water samples.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0), SSN, doParallel, doRNG, spsurvey, shp2graph
License: GPL-2
Imports: rgdal, igraph, foreach, itertools, iterators, RSQLite, DBI, maptools, stringr, ggplot2, MASS, dplyr, methods, sp
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
